cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to recognize the actions and intentions of pedestrians in urban traffic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics and autonomous driving, which suggests the possibility of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of machine learning algorithms indicates the likelihood of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on safety and human factors suggests the possibility of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
